-----BEGIN DECKHAND PROFILE TRUST PLACEHOLDER-----
This file is a placeholder.

The production build of Deckhand will replace this with an
armored PGP keyring containing the active and previous Cepheus
Labs profile-signing public keys. See `docs/PROFILE-TRUST.md` for
the trust model, `docs/RELEASING.md` for rotation procedure.

Deckhand uses this file as a Flutter asset
(packages/deckhand_core/pubspec.yaml -> flutter.assets) and
forwards its contents to the sidecar's `profiles.fetch` method
via the `trusted_keys` parameter. With `require_signed_tag` set
to true at the production wiring site, profile fetches that
don't verify against this keyring are rejected.

While this placeholder is in place, production wiring MUST keep
`require_signed_tag` set to false or fail closed at startup —
shipping with a placeholder *and* signed-tag enforcement on
would brick first launch. The wiring code in app/lib/main.dart
inspects the first line of this file and refuses to enable
strict trust if the marker is still present.
-----END DECKHAND PROFILE TRUST PLACEHOLDER-----
